## M19.1: `unsafe` modifier on a non-callable decl is rejected.
##
## Per GPT-5.5 entry 37 (M21 post-impl review): the `unsafe`
## modifier only makes sense on callable declarations (`fun` /
## `sub` / `extern`). The grammar parses any `unsafe decl` form
## (the `UNSAFE decl -> (unsafe_decl 2)` wrapper composes with
## ANY decl), so sema is where we draw the semantic line.
##
## This also serves as the regression for the `pending_fn_unsafe`
## flag-leak hazard GPT-5.5 caught in entry 37: an earlier draft
## consumed the flag in walkFun via `pending_fn_unsafe = false`,
## which would have leaked the flag to a sibling fn walked after
## an `unsafe struct` declaration. The M19.1 fix lets the
## wrapper's defer/restore own the flag's lifetime exclusively.
## See `unsafe_no_leak_to_sibling_fn.rig` for the leak regression.

unsafe struct S
  x: Int
